      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>2,3-Dimethyl-2,3-butanediol has the common name <i>pinacol.</i> On heating with aqueous acid, pinacol rearranges to <i>pinacolone,</i> 3,3-dimethyl-2-butanone. Suggest a mechanism for this reaction.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ0FXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--462a66c5e4d87bd7d97f442ceae595d9e8e44e5d/OChem_17_EC_048.jpg\" alt=\"Pinacol (2,3-dihydroxy-2,3-dimethylbutane) reacts with hydronium ion to form pinacolone (t-butyl methyl ketone) and water.\">",
